You can give toxdil 20gp and 2 snake glands and he will give you a snake poison (direct damage) back.

I have been given some tier 3 poisons I saw some tier2 poison on a vendor last night, but seeing as I'm only level 22 It wasn't worth the pp (I'm guessing someone had just sold it to the vendor). You can sell the made poison, but you can't transfer a poisoned blade to someone else (or rather, the poison won't go with it).

Seeing as you only have 2 more levels til you can make your own poisons start saving ingredients now! 
Head on over to <A HREF="http://kikyara.tripod.com/poisons/poisontab.html" TARGET="_BLANK">http://kikyara.tripod.com/poisons/poisontab.html</A> for a nice list of poisons by tier. Most of the poisons work by level, so, unless you are just trying to skill up a tier 2 poison won't do any more for you than a tier1 until level 35 or so.

The poison lasts until you zone or use it (1st hit of the fight that the target doesn't resist, backstab doesn't trigger it) While it still gets interupted occasionally, I haven't seen any resisted yet, even by those pesky crocs in oasis that seem to resist most spells. 

For now I'm finding the cistern asps in oasis are the only good source of snake and asp poison sacs (for that area of the continent) and the fire drakes up in lave storm drop the putrid bile about 50% of the time... similar to snake poison, but trivials much high for making and applying, so you can still gain skill.

